SIMPLE: pileated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pileated
<hw>Pi"le*a`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pileatus</ets>, fr.
<ets>pileus</ets> a felt cap or hat.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the
form of a cap for the head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a crest covering the
pileus, or whole top of the head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pileated woodpecker</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
large American woodpecker (<spn>Ceophloeus pileatus</spn>). It is black,
with a bright red pointed crest. Called also <altname>logcock</altname>,
and <altname>woodcock</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piled</ent>⟦br⟧
